Troubleshooting_32_with_32_antivirus.message:
Issues with your Anti-Virus?
Some Anti-virus products may flag and mistakenly identify the %COMPANY% installer as a threat.
Upon release of updates or a new version of software, %COMPANY% distributes signed digital certificates to popular anti-virus vendors. Not all vendors may share our update immediately with their respective user base, which may result in antivirus programs preventing installation on a user’s computer. Please configure your anti-virus software to allow the %COMPANY% installer to run. You may also disable your anti-virus software momentarily, before installing or upgrading %COMPANY% if you continue to experience this issue.

Can't start downloading?
If you clicked Download button and your IE doesn't start downloading %COMPANY% installer, please try following:
1. Close all the IE windows
2. Restart a new IE window
3. Enter "Internet Option" setting dialog
4. Go to "Advanced" tab
5. Click the "Reset..." button in "Reset Internet Explorer settings"
6. Enable the checkbox "Delete personal settings"
7. Click "Reset" and try to download again
